The article discusses the need for immigration reform in the United States, focusing on the negative consequences of open borders. It states that open borders have allowed drugs and gangs to infiltrate vulnerable communities, as well as allowed low-wage workers to compete with the poorest Americans for jobs and wages. President Donald J. Trump is mentioned as someone who aims to ensure the safety of Americans by proposing immigration reforms and providing a permanent solution for Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals (DACA) recipients. The article also suggests that merit-based immigration reform will benefit struggling American communities by benefiting American workers and reducing the strain on Federal resources caused by the current system.